com.nutiteq.geometry
Class Polygon3D

java.lang.Object
  com.nutiteq.geometry.VectorElement
      com.nutiteq.geometry.Polygon3D

public class Polygon3D
extends VectorElement

Geometric prism (defined by base polygon and height) on the map. Base polygons can be non-convex and may contain holes.

Polygon3D

public Polygon3D(java.util.List<MapPos> mapPoses,
                 java.util.List<java.util.List<MapPos>> mapPosesHoles,
                 float height,
                 Label label,
                 Polygon3DStyle polygonStyle,
                 java.lang.Object userData)
Default constructor (can be used if single style is sufficient for all zoom levels).

Parameters:
mapPoses - vertices of the base polygon. Vertices are defined in the coordinate system of the layer this element is attached to.
mapPosesHoles - list of hole polygons. Can be null.
height - height of the prism.
label - the label for the polygon. Label is shown when the polygon is selected. Can be null.
polygonStyle - style for displaying the polygon (color, texture, etc).
userData - custom user data associated with the element.

Parameters:
mapPoses - vertices of the base polygon. Vertices are defined in the coordinate system of the layer this element is attached to.
mapPosesHoles - list of hole polygons. Can be null.
height - height of the prism.
label - the label for the polygon. Label is shown when the polygon is selected. Can be null.
styles - style set defining how to display the polygon.
userData - custom user data associated with the element.
